# SEO-friendly URLs (All Sites)

For any website folder (current or future) in this repo, use **folder routes** (no `.html` in the public URL).

## Required URL structure

- Broker reviews: `/brokers/{broker-name}-review/`
- Comparisons: `/compare/{broker1}-vs-{broker2}/`
- Best lists: `/best/{category}/`
- Guides: `/guides/{article-title}/`

## Slug rules

- Lowercase only
- Hyphens only (no spaces/underscores)
- Generate slugs from the page title / `<h1>` (not manually typed)

## Redirects

If an old URL existed (e.g. `/brokers/libertex.html`), keep it working by creating a **redirect stub HTML** that sends users to the new folder route.

## Automation

Use `scripts/refactor-seo-urls.mjs` to:
- create the new folder routes
- rewrite internal links to the new routes
- generate redirect stubs for old `.html` pages

After URL changes, run:
- `scripts/ensure-seo-meta.mjs`
- `scripts/check-seo-meta.mjs`
- `scripts/generate-sitemaps.mjs`

